; “crow; black; dark”
: From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*ka-n||crow}} (STEDT). Cognate with {{och-l|鴉|crow; raven}}, which retains the earlier vowel in Middle Chinese (''*ʔˠa''), and {{och-l|鸒|jackdaw}}.
: {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} considers it to be {{onomatopoeic|zh|nocap=1}}, and compares it with {{cog|tbq-lol-pro|*akᴸ||crow}}.
: “Black; dark” is a semantic extension of “crow” – “black as a crow”. Compare {{och-l|黑|black}}, which is cognate with {{och-l|墨|ink}}.

; interrogative pronoun
: Related to the following interrogative pronouns with similar phonological shapes in Old Chinese ({{zh-ref|Wang, 1982}}), with differing suffixes:
:* {{och-l|焉|id=3+1|how; where}}
:* {{och-l|惡|id=1|how}}
:* {{och-l|安|where; how; why}}

